{
  "stem": "27351.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there were these big signs-- sign board, no billboards-- epidemics of typhus, beware, keep away, this type of things.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was a very dirty, very empty, in the streets, many windows taped and covered with paper.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it was-- it was quite frightening.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We stayed in this apartment.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And within two weeks, my brother took off.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My father sent some people to smuggle him through the border.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The border at that time was sometimes open, sometimes closed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But it was becoming closed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he joined my father in Bialystok.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I talk about what happened to them later.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Soon afterwards, the border was closed between the Russian part and the German part of Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "People were still going.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But it was not very safe.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And at that point, my father decided that he will get us a visa to come in officially, not to be submitted to the danger of crossing this illegal border.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "This, of course, was a tragic mistake.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And this is how we were stuck with my mother in the Warsaw ghetto.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] You asked me about the street.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "We lived on [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Jelna ?] Street, [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Jelna ?] 17.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Jelna ?] means brave.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And you had to be brave to live there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "We lived on the fourth floor, front room.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We were facing a big and famous Warsaw prison, the [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "From our-- from our window, we could see the [POLISH], the courtyard.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We could see the sentry boxes, and the guards walking around.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "But they could see us too.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And they watched for us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And if they saw anybody in the window, they would shoot.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And sometimes, they were just shooting to amuse themselves.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "So our windows were permanently covered with black paper.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
